rComments: He is probably the nicest prof  I've EVER had. He really adds some life to a really boring subject. He's very understanding of students though, so he'll help you out as much as he can. He treated our classes to pizza twice as well as post-halloween candy. Fair marker too and doesn't expect anything insane from students.

It doesn't get any better than this. Professor Frey did an amazing job teaching occasionally dry material. He adjusted the course's pace to accomadate midterms in other courses and spent a few lectures (with free food!) talking about applications of probability to his very interesting research. I wish he could teach all my courses.

Amazing prof in terms of clarity and explanations. Honestly, I can say Prof. Frey is the nicest guy I have ever seen in my entire life - he bought pizza for the whole class, AND free candy on halloween!
best prof ever!  He's funny and energetic.  Best prof in UofT for sure.
Clear, enthusiastic lecturer. Very understanding and approachable. Awesome prof.
